name: Rosehaven
overview: When Daniel returns to his hometown, Rosehaven, to take over his family's troubled real estate business, he's surprisingly joined by his best (city) friend Emma - who's on the run from a marriage that didn't last the honeymoon. Between Daniel's crippling anxiety and Emma's exuberant irresponsibility will they be able to save the business? It seems unlikely, but it will be fun to watch them try. And might their friendship mean more than they realise?

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Daniel returns to his rural Tasmanian hometown to help his mother with her real estate business. To his surprise, his best friend Emma turns up on his doorstep on the run from her marriage.Â

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: It's Daniel and Emma's first day in the office and already they are facing unique difficulties of running a real estate agency in a small town.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Emma makes life difficult for Daniel by accidently uploading some heavily photo shopped pictures of a property right before it's to be viewed by potential buyers.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Daniel's childhood cubby house has been overrun by his old school bully Bruce. Emma convinces Daniel to confront Bruce and get his cubby house back.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Barbara has returned home & for the first time Mother & Son are working together. Daniel is determined to impress Barbara by expanding McCallum Real Estate's profile within the town by offering free door-to-door appraisals.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Emma is on thin ice with Barbara after allowing a bunch of random strangers to trash her house. Emma is determined to make amends by following Daniel's advice: be more professional.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Daniel has been opening some of Barbara's mail and discovers that McCallum Real Estate is in real financial trouble. He tells Emma he has an idea on how to make some cuts.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Daniel tells Emma that he and his girlfriend Grace are leaving Rosehaven for good. This leaves Emma with the choice of staying on without him or going back to Melbourne to try and get her old job back.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Daniel returns to Rosehaven, to find he must yet again prove himself at McCallum Real Estate where best friend Emma has been promoted.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Barbara won't make a speech at the local primary school (or do tuckshop duty), and a reluctant Daniel steps in. But his resolve is put to the test when he and Emma are accused of stealing.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Emma is planning a birthday party for Daniel, while Daniel is determined to list a house for sale.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: When a blackout plunges Rosehaven into darkness, evening plans are thrown into turmoil.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: It's sales vs rentals as Daniel and Emma take sides in a neighbourly dispute. Daniel is desperate to hold on to the listing, so he agrees to help Steve, with an unusual complaint about an adornment on his neighbour's house.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Rosehaven is under siege with a nocturnal graffiti artist on the loose. Emma is keen to investigate.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: It's the annual Rosehaven Hops Festival and Emma is determined to prove to one and all that she belongs in Rosehaven.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: With his first auction looming, Emma is helping Daniel practice his auctioning skills.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: When the professionalism of McCallum Real Estate is brought into question, Daniel tries to fix their reputation while Emma befriends a pig.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Emma and Daniel try to prevent a tenant from moving house, after he finds out that the previous owner died in the house and the neighbours are eager to pay their respects. Emma and Daniel come up with a unique fix.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Can people change, or do they just stay the same? Barbara's sold her house and a visit from her sister, Jenny, leads to some uncharted territory for the McCallums.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Daniel and Emma are on a drive out of town looking to secure a listing but the day takes a turn as they find themselves getting lost.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Emma is at home, sick, and feeling very sorry for herself. Grace and Daniel go to check on her, but Daniel keeps his distance - after all, he doesn't want to get sick.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: It's Valentine's Day and Emma is out at Farmer Dan's house. It's an early start and they're off to fix a fence. She's clearly out of place - farm life doesn't come naturally to her, nor is being up this early.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Daniel and Grace get a new housemate and Emma lands McCallum Real Estate in hot water with a new block of land she is trying to sell.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Rosehaven are boycotting McCallum Real Estate so Emma and Daniel go into overdrive to try and put things right.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: It's a time of change in Rosehaven and while Daniel seems to be managing it best, it might be Emma, despite her playful misadventures, who offers the most grown up advice.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: After spending a lot of time together - just the two of them - Daniel and Emma decide to host an audition to add a third member to their dream team.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Emotions run high in Rosehaven before they realise that all everyone has in common is that they want to be liked. And Emma babysits a rabbit.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Emma, Daniel and Barbara head to the Regional Realtors Association of Tasmania Conference, where Barbara is hot property amongst the other agents. Emma sees an opportunity for Daniel to meet someone.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: ts a rare warm and sunny day in Rosehaven as Daniel discovers there may be some karma involved in rejecting money from an old lady to buy ice-cream.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Daniel's morning is set into a spin when he discovers a new attractive pharmacist at the chemist. Emma decides that it's time for them to get back out there as they go online to find love.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Everyone's wishing Emma a happy birthday, but she's not a fan of celebrating. It's work experience week and McCallum Real Estate haven't had any requests until Gez from the op shop asks if she can learn.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: When a flashy competitor sets his sights on Rosehaven will the locals be enticed by the bells and whistles over the local knowledge of McCallum Real Estate?

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Daniel and Emma are keeping busy at McCallum Real Estate as Barbara lets them take on more responsibility. It may be the year she finally retires.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Emma has a new magic eight ball; Daniel has a health scare that leads to a confronting situation with his ex, Grace, and together they try to solve a problem with an overbearing landlord.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Grace organises a fun run that only Daniel and Emma turn up to. After they try to resolve a relationship problem they work out a way to show Grace just how much the town cares.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Emma and Daniel witness the Rosehaven Bakery get robbed and they take it upon themselves to try and solve the crime.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Always looking for new ways to drum up business, Barbara tells Daniel and Emma to sign up for a cooking competition which will hopefully result in a new dish on the pub menu with naming rights.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Daniel and Emma lead a group of potential buyers to the countryside blind folded in an effort to sell a property without saying where it is.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: It's time for Barbara to choose a successor, and it might not be the obvious choice.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Barbara's retirement isn't going to plan. She's retraining and needs the help of Daniel and Emma.
